Anambra State government has arrested 50 persons and charged them with evading revenue payment and other levies in markets, Commissioner for Commerce, Industry and Wealth Creation Dr. Christian Madubuko has said. He said yesterday that more than N150million had been recovered from them. Madubuko told reporters in Awka that the recovery was made between March and August. He said the arrests were made because of the effect on the state’s revenue. Madubuko said: “For some time now, we have been having problems with revenue thieves in markets. Those arrested have been arraigned. If they are found guilty they will be fined and if they refuse to pay, they will go to jail. “Since I came into office, over 50 persons have been arrested and they have paid. “The government has zero tolerance for revenue thieves. It has resolved to ensure recovery of revenues belonging to the state.”  